* 
Earlier today Alfred Thompson lamented over some of the [[http://blog.acthompson.net/2017/11/cant-we-computer-science-people-all.html][discord]] that
has surfaced recently in the in the CS Ed community. There has been a
number of public disagreements in the community recently but that's
not a surprise. When the community was young it was easy for everyone
to pat each other on the back even when people didn't necessarily
agree on product and process. Now that CS Ed is big time and there's
more at stake there was bound to be some fragmentation.

While Alfred raised a lot of great points the twitter thread (since
deleted) that I think partly inspired the post originated from
somewhere else.

